1
00:00:56,916 --> 00:01:01,276
 I asked him to cut it in half,

2
00:01:01,842 --> 00:01:03,592
my day starts.

3
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,266
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:25,666 --> 00:01:28,958
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:34,563 --> 00:01:36,062
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:36,578 --> 00:01:38,620
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:40,948 --> 00:01:43,461
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:43,461 --> 00:01:48,711
YAKISOBA DOG

9
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,118
We don't keep bread,
because we mainly serve rice.

10
00:01:57,958 --> 00:02:01,291
If some customers
really want to eat sandwiches,

11
00:02:01,641 --> 00:02:03,849
they bring their own bread.

12
00:02:04,205 --> 00:02:05,288
Here you go.

13
00:02:07,803 --> 00:02:08,993
Welcome.

14
00:02:08,993 --> 00:02:11,276
Master, make me the usual
with these, please.

15
00:02:11,958 --> 00:02:13,583
You brought so many again today.

16
00:02:14,562 --> 00:02:16,351
Please serve some to everyone
if they want.

17
00:02:16,351 --> 00:02:17,185
Okay.

18
00:02:41,175 --> 00:02:41,875
Here you are.

19
00:02:44,083 --> 00:02:45,416
This is the one!

20
00:02:46,538 --> 00:02:53,121
Mr. Kotani is a successful businessman
who runs cat cafés and dog cafés,

21
00:02:53,724 --> 00:02:58,224
but somehow he always orders
this yakisoba sandwich here.

22
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:02,988
What's the point of putting
yakisoba noodles between bread?

23
00:03:02,988 --> 00:03:04,990
They both contain carbohydrates, right?

24
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:07,895
I agree. Just looking at it makes me full.

25
00:03:07,895 --> 00:03:09,641
That's why it's great.

26
00:03:09,641 --> 00:03:12,516
Meat and carbohydrates
are essential to our youth, right?

27
00:03:12,864 --> 00:03:14,114
Our youth.

28
00:03:15,071 --> 00:03:17,604
Mr. Kotani, you seem to be so happy today.

29
00:03:18,077 --> 00:03:19,786
Has anything good happened to you?

30
00:03:20,863 --> 00:03:22,071
Thank you for asking!

31
00:03:22,826 --> 00:03:24,097
My high school will participate

32
00:03:24,097 --> 00:03:26,243
in the Spring National Invitational
High School Baseball Tournament.

33
00:03:26,243 --> 00:03:27,452
For the first time in 40 years!

34
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,647
Congratulations.

35
00:03:29,647 --> 00:03:31,187
Well done!

36
00:03:31,187 --> 00:03:33,508
They did their best.

37
00:03:33,508 --> 00:03:35,488
Were you in the baseball club?

38
00:03:35,488 --> 00:03:37,242
Yeah, as a substitute, though.

39
00:03:37,734 --> 00:03:40,633
One of my classmates back then
is the manager now.

40
00:03:42,854 --> 00:03:44,146
Please give him a glass.

41
00:03:46,294 --> 00:03:48,475
Congrats. Would you like some?

42
00:03:48,977 --> 00:03:50,519
Yes, please.

43
00:03:52,324 --> 00:03:56,391
Ryu doesn't look like it,
but he played baseball in high school.

44
00:03:56,836 --> 00:03:58,840
So I guess he understands
very well how he feels.

45
00:04:05,968 --> 00:04:09,280
That manager promised me once

46
00:04:10,351 --> 00:04:14,059
that he'd make sure to take his students
to Koshien Stadium one day.

47
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:17,931
He kept his promise for sure.

48
00:04:21,048 --> 00:04:21,881
Yes.

49
00:04:25,314 --> 00:04:27,064
No need to cry.

50
00:04:32,286 --> 00:04:33,618
Let's celebrate!

51
00:04:33,957 --> 00:04:36,514
Master, beer for everyone. They're on me!

52
00:04:36,514 --> 00:04:37,348
Sure.

53
00:04:43,374 --> 00:04:44,416
Mr. Kotani!

54
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:47,659
Long time no see!

55
00:04:47,659 --> 00:04:49,845
Let's go for a drink!

56
00:04:49,845 --> 00:04:56,428
He must be so happy that
he's been drinking every day since.

57
00:04:58,585 --> 00:05:00,389
He was so drunk.

58
00:05:00,821 --> 00:05:04,893
He stood up and started singing
his school song.

59
00:05:05,036 --> 00:05:07,446
He made a mess at my bar, too.

60
00:05:08,505 --> 00:05:10,154
At your place, too?

61
00:05:10,221 --> 00:05:11,411
That's right.

62
00:05:11,799 --> 00:05:15,506
He kept talking to
other customers persistently,

63
00:05:15,506 --> 00:05:18,155
so I told him off, saying, "Stop it!"

64
00:05:19,401 --> 00:05:21,616
You should've told him off, too, Master.

65
00:05:22,903 --> 00:05:24,361
Next time he comes around.

66
00:05:25,358 --> 00:05:26,740
Give him a break.

67
00:05:27,162 --> 00:05:30,803
He works hard as the head of the company.

68
00:05:31,259 --> 00:05:33,852
He must feel so pleased and nostalgic.

69
00:05:34,446 --> 00:05:36,376
I like high school baseball games.

70
00:05:36,856 --> 00:05:39,485
Young baseball players
tickle my motherly instinct.

71
00:05:39,485 --> 00:05:42,469
I want to treat them with lots of food.

72
00:05:42,632 --> 00:05:45,541
But they're the ones
who achieved the result, right?

73
00:05:46,703 --> 00:05:50,745
Do high school baseball games
make adults get excited so much?

74
00:05:51,214 --> 00:05:52,356
In spring and summer.

75
00:05:52,751 --> 00:05:54,542
Isn't it one of the Japanese traditions?

76
00:05:54,882 --> 00:05:57,398
What's wrong with getting excited
twice a year?

77
00:05:57,788 --> 00:06:00,163
You're consistently excited
throughout the year.

78
00:06:00,832 --> 00:06:01,876
Right?

79
00:06:04,218 --> 00:06:06,677
What's wrong with Mr. Kotani?

80
00:06:07,882 --> 00:06:10,632
He'd never been that drunk before.

81
00:06:17,997 --> 00:06:19,289
Crap.

82
00:06:29,115 --> 00:06:30,294
Thanks for the other night.

83
00:06:33,083 --> 00:06:35,375
You're good!

84
00:06:36,288 --> 00:06:37,941
Have you played baseball before?

85
00:06:38,522 --> 00:06:40,735
You're so bad.
Is it true you were in the club?

86
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:43,958
Were you watching me?

87
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:48,112
I haven't played at all
since I was a high school student.

88
00:06:48,562 --> 00:06:50,091
I've got some blisters on my hand.

89
00:06:54,616 --> 00:06:57,658
But it's so nice
to play sometimes, isn't it?

90
00:06:58,858 --> 00:07:00,640
It reminds me of high school days.

91
00:07:04,444 --> 00:07:05,676
Nice batting!

92
00:07:18,435 --> 00:07:19,981
Your form is not right.

93
00:07:20,394 --> 00:07:21,074
What?

94
00:07:22,074 --> 00:07:24,931
If you keep batting,
you'll get the right feeling back.

95
00:07:24,931 --> 00:07:28,056
You won't easily forget
what you learned kinesthetically.

96
00:07:36,128 --> 00:07:37,128
Here.

97
00:07:38,613 --> 00:07:41,279
I'm sorry for being so drunk
the other day.

98
00:07:42,858 --> 00:07:44,681
I understand how happy you are,

99
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:47,441
but don't you think
you drink too much lately?

100
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:54,264
Look at this.

101
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:58,503
MANAGER YOKOKAWA

102
00:07:58,503 --> 00:08:01,183
"Keep making small efforts.
MANAGER YOKOKAWA

103
00:08:01,183 --> 00:08:02,650
I want my students to believe in themselves,
MANAGER YOKOKAWA

104
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:04,984
and to play their baseball games
to the fullest."

105
00:08:05,608 --> 00:08:07,914
He's a good manager, Mr. Yokokawa.

106
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:09,250
Right?

107
00:08:10,868 --> 00:08:14,618
We both went to the university here
after graduating from high school.

108
00:08:15,470 --> 00:08:17,459
During summer vacation, when we were 20,

109
00:08:17,459 --> 00:08:21,088
he told me to walk home to our hometown
in Kōchi prefecture. So I walked with him.

110
00:08:21,578 --> 00:08:23,782
On foot? Why?

111
00:08:24,368 --> 00:08:26,951
He played baseball in university,

112
00:08:27,611 --> 00:08:29,152
but he injured his shoulder.

113
00:08:29,697 --> 00:08:32,280
I think he was thinking
about his choices ahead.

114
00:08:35,013 --> 00:08:38,686
It was when we were walking
a straight road along Suruga Bay,

115
00:08:38,686 --> 00:08:40,311
if I remember correctly.

116
00:08:41,775 --> 00:08:47,150
We bought a yakisoba sandwich,
the last one at a shop, and we shared it.

117
00:08:50,608 --> 00:08:52,316
Yokokawa!

118
00:08:54,379 --> 00:08:55,549
Let's take a break!

119
00:09:00,688 --> 00:09:01,921
Hey!

120
00:09:03,930 --> 00:09:05,555
Shut up and keep walking!

121
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:13,769
Then he told me...

122
00:09:15,462 --> 00:09:19,546
"If I can make it home,
I'd continue playing baseball.

123
00:09:20,645 --> 00:09:22,637
As I can't be a professional
baseball player any more,

124
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:27,177
I'll be a high school teacher
and take my students to Koshien Stadium."

125
00:09:29,086 --> 00:09:30,848
You told me the other day.

126
00:09:33,544 --> 00:09:36,202
He made it home on foot, but I couldn't.

127
00:09:36,787 --> 00:09:40,328
I got diarrhea on the way
and went back to Tokyo by myself.

128
00:09:40,328 --> 00:09:41,411
I see.

129
00:09:43,309 --> 00:09:46,600
But I felt for sure at that time

130
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:49,010
that I should do something.

131
00:09:50,045 --> 00:09:53,057
Because I couldn't live like Yokokawa.

132
00:09:53,727 --> 00:09:56,171
Do you still see him?

133
00:09:57,121 --> 00:10:00,871
Not at all after he graduated from
university and went back to our hometown.

134
00:10:01,716 --> 00:10:05,133
I haven't paid him back

135
00:10:06,061 --> 00:10:07,477
the money I owe him.

136
00:10:08,706 --> 00:10:09,998
I see.

137
00:10:12,451 --> 00:10:15,160
In that case, why don't you
donate the money to his school?

138
00:10:15,758 --> 00:10:18,966
It'd cost a lot of money to go
to the national tournament, wouldn't it?

139
00:10:19,886 --> 00:10:20,886
Donation.

140
00:10:23,453 --> 00:10:25,036
That's not a bad idea.

141
00:11:12,115 --> 00:11:13,199
Hello?

142
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:16,016
Are you Kotani?

143
00:11:16,921 --> 00:11:18,088
It's me.

144
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:27,516
I talked to Yokokawa
for the first time in 30 years.

145
00:11:28,569 --> 00:11:32,848
He called me
because he learned about my donation.

146
00:11:34,838 --> 00:11:35,921
That's great.

147
00:11:36,990 --> 00:11:38,355
Thanks to you, Master.

148
00:11:39,579 --> 00:11:42,266
I didn't do anything.
I just thought of an idea.

149
00:11:42,925 --> 00:11:44,425
He remembered, too.

150
00:11:45,308 --> 00:11:47,016
He said to me on the phone...

151
00:11:48,016 --> 00:11:50,100
I finally kept my promise.

152
00:11:54,259 --> 00:11:55,134
Here.

153
00:11:56,749 --> 00:12:00,548
I wrapped them all up as you told me.
Do you want something to eat?

154
00:12:00,548 --> 00:12:03,571
No, thank you.
I'm going somewhere far away.

155
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:09,054
Here. I don't need the change.
Please keep it.

156
00:12:09,054 --> 00:12:10,804
Okay. Thank you.

157
00:12:17,071 --> 00:12:19,613
Master, thank you.

158
00:12:37,183 --> 00:12:38,641
By the way,

159
00:12:39,427 --> 00:12:43,930
when I walked past Mr. Kotani's cat café,
it was closed.

160
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:45,514
Really?

161
00:12:46,259 --> 00:12:48,622
I thought it was popular, wasn't it?

162
00:12:48,622 --> 00:12:50,482
I heard so, too,

163
00:12:51,051 --> 00:12:55,010
but according to the note, a new Taiwanese
tapioca shop will open next month.

164
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:57,899
Tapioca? What's that?

165
00:12:58,934 --> 00:13:01,791
Don't you know? Tapioca.

166
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,202
Tapioca?

167
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:05,225
Tapioca.

168
00:13:05,653 --> 00:13:06,778
Welcome.

169
00:13:07,871 --> 00:13:09,829
Has the guy called Kotani been around?

170
00:13:10,855 --> 00:13:11,897
Mr. Kotani?

171
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,595
I haven't seen him lately.

172
00:13:19,479 --> 00:13:20,813
I see. That's fine.

173
00:13:26,076 --> 00:13:27,284
What was that about?

174
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:30,050
A loan shark.

175
00:13:33,211 --> 00:13:34,836
They're not very nice.

176
00:13:39,050 --> 00:13:41,150
Kotani, come out!

177
00:13:41,150 --> 00:13:42,622
You're there, aren't you?

178
00:13:42,622 --> 00:13:44,008
According to Ryu,

179
00:13:44,008 --> 00:13:44,628
OVERDUE PAYMENT REMINDER LETTER
According to Ryu,

180
00:13:44,628 --> 00:13:46,068
OVERDUE PAYMENT REMINDER LETTER
Mr. Kotani...

181
00:13:46,068 --> 00:13:48,810
OVERDUE PAYMENT REMINDER LETTER
...his business had gone bad,

182
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:52,190
OVERDUE PAYMENT REMINDER LETTER
and he borrowed one million yen from the company...

183
00:13:52,190 --> 00:13:54,025
and disappeared.

184
00:13:54,410 --> 00:13:56,537
Come out, you! Hey!

185
00:13:56,537 --> 00:14:01,970
Looking back at how drunk he was getting,
he might have felt desperate.

186
00:14:04,008 --> 00:14:07,508
He looked so happy when he talked
about his donation to his school.

187
00:14:08,178 --> 00:14:10,011
Maybe the money also came from...

188
00:14:10,966 --> 00:14:12,235
Probably.

189
00:14:13,117 --> 00:14:15,659
He can't come back to this town.

190
00:14:36,236 --> 00:14:39,551
It must be nearly the end
of the hay fever season, right?

191
00:14:39,936 --> 00:14:43,186
I'm allergic to Japanese cypress,
not to Japanese cedar.

192
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:45,207
I'm fed up with this.

193
00:14:48,542 --> 00:14:49,368
Welcome.

194
00:14:49,712 --> 00:14:50,582
Good evening.

195
00:14:53,978 --> 00:14:55,570
Are you, perhaps...

196
00:14:56,426 --> 00:14:58,097
I'm Yokokawa. Nice to meet you.

197
00:14:59,417 --> 00:15:02,775
This is the classmate of Mr. Kotani
and the manager he was talking about.

198
00:15:03,883 --> 00:15:05,175
Is that so?

199
00:15:05,716 --> 00:15:08,050
I learned about the donation from Kotani.

200
00:15:08,879 --> 00:15:11,667
He told me this diner's Master
had suggested he do it.

201
00:15:12,407 --> 00:15:13,191
Yeah.

202
00:15:14,549 --> 00:15:15,698
Thank you very much.

203
00:15:16,695 --> 00:15:17,888
Is beer okay for you?

204
00:15:18,462 --> 00:15:19,008
Yes.

205
00:15:19,242 --> 00:15:20,404
It's on me.

206
00:15:20,890 --> 00:15:22,900
To celebrate the participation
in the tournament.

207
00:15:23,193 --> 00:15:25,212
Thank you, but...

208
00:15:26,755 --> 00:15:28,005
Excuse me.

209
00:15:33,579 --> 00:15:36,746
That was a close game, wasn't it?

210
00:15:37,725 --> 00:15:39,142
We lost badly.

211
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:43,544
We managed to hit back and score
in the last inning at least,

212
00:15:44,414 --> 00:15:46,755
and avoided a shutout game.

213
00:15:46,755 --> 00:15:51,207
It's wonderful just to
participate in the tournament.

214
00:15:51,628 --> 00:15:52,587
That's right.

215
00:15:52,878 --> 00:15:54,003
Thank you.

216
00:16:00,464 --> 00:16:06,088
I wish Mr. Kotani were as honest
as you are, even 10% as much as you.

217
00:16:08,651 --> 00:16:10,008
You know about...

218
00:16:10,766 --> 00:16:12,266
his debt, is that correct?

219
00:16:14,921 --> 00:16:18,046
He came all the way to the stadium.

220
00:16:18,906 --> 00:16:20,573
Did you see him?

221
00:16:21,173 --> 00:16:25,590
Yes. He told me about the debt
at the time.

222
00:16:27,247 --> 00:16:28,872
I haven't seen him since then.

223
00:16:31,006 --> 00:16:32,610
We made a promise to meet up here.

224
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,367
Meet him? Here?

225
00:16:36,225 --> 00:16:36,958
Yes.

226
00:16:41,725 --> 00:16:42,592
Ryu!

227
00:16:44,328 --> 00:16:46,578
Master, make me the usual
with these, please.

228
00:16:48,169 --> 00:16:48,899
Sure.

229
00:17:01,785 --> 00:17:03,368
This is Mr. Kenzaki.

230
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:06,204
He helped me so much
with the recent event.

231
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:08,351
This is Yokokawa.

232
00:17:08,351 --> 00:17:11,425
The manager of my high school team
I told you about the other day.

233
00:17:11,855 --> 00:17:13,862
I wish your team good luck
for the summer tournament.

234
00:17:15,125 --> 00:17:16,041
Thank you.

235
00:17:17,642 --> 00:17:23,767
I thought about killing myself by jumping
off a cliff after watching their game.

236
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:30,416
He told me off, saying,
"It's so silly to die because of money."

237
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:33,833
That's why I came back here.

238
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,301
Then I bumped into him in a batting cage.

239
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:42,058
Then, he sorted things out for you?

240
00:17:42,058 --> 00:17:42,891
Yes, he did.

241
00:17:43,718 --> 00:17:45,510
After Mr. Kenzaki talked to them,

242
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:47,702
they postponed the due date,

243
00:17:48,054 --> 00:17:50,221
and they even reduced the interest.

244
00:17:51,326 --> 00:17:55,368
Thank you so much for saving my life.

245
00:17:58,572 --> 00:18:00,187
You should choose your friends.

246
00:18:00,541 --> 00:18:02,083
For your students, too.

247
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:15,291
I'll make sure that he
keeps his promise to you.

248
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:24,546
Wait...

249
00:18:25,139 --> 00:18:28,092
Yokokawa, what do you mean by that?

250
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:30,385
Mr. Kotani...

251
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:33,875
you're so clueless.

252
00:18:35,125 --> 00:18:37,901
If you miss paying back your debt,

253
00:18:37,901 --> 00:18:42,939
Ryu also needs to take
responsibility, as he protected you.

254
00:18:46,494 --> 00:18:49,494
Ryu is too nice.

255
00:18:56,407 --> 00:18:59,157
I was so happy about your donation.

256
00:19:00,706 --> 00:19:04,831
I'd be happier if the money
wasn't from the loan company.

257
00:19:09,379 --> 00:19:10,441
Here you are.

258
00:19:12,702 --> 00:19:16,155
Mr. Kotani always orders this.

259
00:19:19,562 --> 00:19:23,645
When I was in university,
we tried to walk to our hometown.

260
00:19:24,365 --> 00:19:26,401
We shared this on the way.

261
00:19:26,634 --> 00:19:29,305
Yes, he told me about it.

262
00:19:30,981 --> 00:19:33,689
At first, he said, "I won't eat it.

263
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:39,251
I don't get hungry, because I don't play
sports as much as you do."

264
00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:41,295
A weird theory.

265
00:19:42,324 --> 00:19:44,074
But his stomach was rumbling.

266
00:19:45,581 --> 00:19:45,855
So,

267
00:19:46,857 --> 00:19:49,096
I asked him to cut it in half,
and then he did...

268
00:19:55,087 --> 00:19:56,074
Like this.

269
00:19:57,177 --> 00:19:59,655
It's not even at all.

270
00:20:03,184 --> 00:20:05,399
He looked at me like a puppy.

271
00:20:07,190 --> 00:20:08,524
He gave me...

272
00:20:09,951 --> 00:20:11,576
the bigger one.

273
00:20:15,424 --> 00:20:16,997
That's a nice story.

274
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:22,875
That's the time when you were depressed...

275
00:20:23,950 --> 00:20:26,366
because you couldn't
play baseball any more.

276
00:20:31,032 --> 00:20:32,490
At that time...

277
00:20:33,717 --> 00:20:37,384
when I saw the wistful look on your face,

278
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:41,116
I felt so much better.

279
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:47,075
I felt like thinking
about my future a little, like,

280
00:20:49,325 --> 00:20:50,783
"Even not as a player,

281
00:20:52,373 --> 00:20:55,040
I can be involved with
baseball in different ways."

282
00:21:00,333 --> 00:21:03,749
You made us go to Koshien Stadium.

283
00:21:08,213 --> 00:21:11,797
I'm sure you can get over this.

284
00:21:13,425 --> 00:21:15,217
It's my turn to support you.

285
00:21:58,504 --> 00:21:59,587
Eat this.

286
00:23:42,382 --> 00:23:47,405
THIS STORY IS A WORK OF FICTION

